                    <div class="margin">
                      <h3>Add a Camera</h3>
                      <p>After you installed the newest version of Evocam please start the program, then open the preferences window.</p>
                      <br>
                      <div>
                          <amp-img role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/SecuritySpy_01.png" width="800" height="651" layout="responsive" class="shadow"></amp-img>
                      </div>
                      <br>
                      <p>Go to Settings and open the Camera Settings.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                      <div>
                          <amp-img role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/SecuritySpy_02.png" width="800" height="653" layout="responsive" class="shadow"></amp-img>
                      </div>
                      <br>
                      <p>Choose your camera model and type in your camera´s IP address, it's ports (default: 80 &amp; 554) and your login. Click on Ok.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                      <div>
                          <amp-img role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/SecuritySpy_03.png" width="800" height="654" layout="responsive" class="shadow"></amp-img>
                      </div>
                      <br>
                      <p>And Done - your surveillance is up &amp; running.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                      <h3>Alarm Function</h3>
                      <br>
                      <div>
                          <amp-img role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/SecuritySpy_04.png" width="800" height="704" layout="responsive" class="shadow"></amp-img>
                      </div>
                      <br>
                      <p>Click on Setup to configure your camera´s Motion Detection.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                      <div>
                          <amp-img role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/SecuritySpy_05.png" width="800" height="700" layout="responsive" class="shadow"></amp-img>
                      </div>
                      <br>
                      <p>Select if you want to record your camera´s audio stream and if you want audio above a threshold to trigger an alert.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                      <div>
                          <amp-img role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/SecuritySpy_08.png" width="800" height="706" layout="responsive" class="shadow"></amp-img>
                      </div>
                      <br>
                      <p>The alarm actions - like an <a href="/Motion_Detection/Alarm_Notification">email notification</a> (see also Email notification setup - is configured in the tab Actions.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                      <h3>Recording</h3>
                      <br>
                      <div>
                          <amp-img role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/SecuritySpy_06.png" width="800" height="711" layout="responsive" class="shadow"></amp-img>
                      </div>
                      <br>
                      <p>Use snapshots to create a Timelapse video. Or upload snapshots to an <a href="/Motion_Detection/FTP_Server_Setup">FTP server</a> or your <a href="/Motion_Detection/Router_as_a_FTP_Server">Router</a>.</p>
